Description

Specifications: input voltage: 120 V AC, 60 hz, output voltage: 24 V AC at 40 VA, dimensions: 2 x 2. 5 x 2. 5 inch universal powering for multiple doorbell chimes, smart video doorbells and thermostatic devices in one home. Replace the old and under powered doorbell transformers for better performance. Compatible with Ring Pro and ring doorbells, Wi-Fi and other smart thermostats like Nest and Eco bee and more. Not compatible with ring chime pro. UL Certified to safety and quality. Safe and easy install I on. WARNING: This product may expose you to chemicals known to the State of California to cause cancer or reproductive harm

Features & details

Features

  • 24VAC/40VA doorbell transformer for powering single or multiple doorbells and thermostats.
  • Thermal cut-off switch offers an extra layer of safety, shutting off power in the event of excessive temperature. UL Certified.
  • Quick and easy installation: simply mount to electrical box via threaded connector or screw down
  • Eliminate issues caused by underpowered transformers: a lack of power, connection issues, low quality video resolution, and low chime volume may be an indicator of an underpowered transformer
  • Compatible with Ring Video Doorbell Pro, Nest Hello, Nest thermostats, Zmodo Smart Greet Wi-Fi Doorbell, Sky Bell Doorbell, and more. Brands mentioned for compatibility information only.
  • Input voltage: 120 Vac, 60Hz | Output voltage: 24 Vac at 40VA
  • Backed by a 2 year manufacturer

    5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
    Works great. Easy Install.
    Reviewed in the United States on January 11, 2025
    Style: 24V, 40VA
    I fixed my RING doorbell problems. It was not charging, wouldn't stay connected to Wi-Fi, nor ring the old mechanical doorbell in the kitchen. The old transformer was only 10 va (approx 10 watts). This one has 4x the output, (max recommended by RING) and everything now... See more
    I fixed my RING doorbell problems. It was not charging, wouldn't stay connected to Wi-Fi, nor ring the old mechanical doorbell in the kitchen. The old transformer was only 10 va (approx 10 watts). This one has 4x the output, (max recommended by RING) and everything now works great.
    Took a little time to find where the old one was hidden in the basement. It was wired in beside one of the basement lights. Turn off power before you do anything. In my case, flipped the breaker and the light turned off.
    Easier installing this new one than it was taking out the old one. The old one had screws in side of the junction box to mount it. This one has a threaded stem that goes thru the knock-out with a plastic nut. Easy to mount. Connect the bell rings and then the green, white, and black wires. Stuff all the wires back into the box and screw on the cover plate. Last, turn the power back on and check it works.

It was easy to install and yes, now the inside chime works. Like I said, I might have gotten along without it, but now the chime isn't just sitting there doing nothing. Great price, fast delivery, easy install, solved the problem. Hope this helps.

    I installed a new Ring Pro doorbell and my old 10V transformer wasn't powerful enough for this. I upgraded the transformer with this 24V 40vA model. Perfect choice to the job at hand. I didn't want to thinker inside my main breaker box to swap with the old transformer. I bought an electrical box and a closed cover for it ( around $3 for both). I popped out one of the side and screwed the transformer to it. I then used a three wire electrical cord that was on an old toaster oven that I had kept. I connected the wires and screwed the transformer to the wall. I just plug the new transformer in a standard outlet and left the old 10V transformer in the main breaker box.
